headline.main: NAZIS BLAME BRITISH FOR PEACE RUMORS; Profess Annoyances -- Say Eden and Churchill Must Go

lead_paragraph: BERLIN, Oct. 13 -- Annoyance at "British-fed rumors about German peace feelers" constitutes one of the main themes of the Berlin press today. They are once more called "ludicrous inventions" aimed at fooling the people at home into thinking that the Reich is exhausted and anxious or peace.
abstract: Berlin press annoyed at rumors of German peace feelers; blames Brit
